      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency analysis of input parameters between validation and COU conditions is not required at MRL 2. Qualitative similarity has been established under the Relevance of Validation Activities factor. Factor is not-assessed per the MRL 2 matrix."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team has reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors for COU1. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were determined to be not-assessed at MRL 2. Of the seven assessed factors, six achieved their required gradation levels without qualification. The Test Conditions factor was assessed at Gradation 2 against a required level of Gradation 3; however, the team determined that the totality of evidence — including the high fidelity of inlet flow rate matching (±1.5%), viscosity agreement within 2.3%, a dedicated thermal sensitivity study, five years of institutional experience with analogous FDA pump protocols, and corroborating expert judgment from two independent specialists — provides adequate practical confidence in the representativeness of the simulated test conditions. The residual gap in formal boundary condition documentation is considered low-risk given that the model influence is rated Medium and independent bench testing will confirm the worst-case operating point identified by CFD prior to regulatory submission. On balance, the evidence is judged sufficient to support the intended use of the model for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions, and the package is Accepted at Model Risk Level 2 for a Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
